metadata.name: Art blocks II #89
metadata.description:
Art Blocks II was built on a dynamic grid system. Blocks with random colors and sizes represent the poetic aesthetics of generative art and the harmony of randomness. This collection is composed of 11 different grid sizes and 4 different patterns of backgrounds with more than 150 color palettes. There will be a roughly 14% chance of getting colorful gradients in the work.

This collection works the best in full size. Enlarge it to see the details :)

- Press "s" to save the image in 4800 × 3200

metadata.name: Elephant school #47
metadata.description: I remain a student all my life until sometimes I enter the elephant school because all creatures are my teachers and I am a student of all of them and always learn from them.

metadata.name: Living City #16
metadata.description:
It is a "Living City"

The state of the city sky will change by receiving your current time.
For example, if it is morning in your city, the sun will rise in your mint, and if it is night, your mint will be dark.

The settings are such that at 06:00 in your geographical area, the sun rises and the sky slowly brightens, and at 19:00 in your geographical area, the sky darkens and the sun sets. In the rest of the night, the moon will shine in the sky and the position of the moon in the sky will change every hour of the night.

To see this effect better, you can take a photo of each watch and compare the photos.

- Press “s” to save the current canvas.

* Note: If it is night in your geographical location, you will definitely see the minted pieces with a dark sky with the moon, and if it is day, you will see a bright sky with a random background color with the sun.

--
Artist: Pointiago
Aug 02, 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: REIN #55
metadata.description:
REIN

A generative approach to personal interpretation of reincarnation

It is not my right and job to prove the existence of reincarnation, but the concept makes a good dialogue for my heart and also is a fun challenge for my brain.

1. About the role:

The element on the screen is basically the metaphor for every object/person in your current life.

As the ACTOR, you can make choice under your instant willingness and travel in this world with limited time.

As the OBSERVER you can watch the above and question and dialogue with the ACTOR and alter its choice.

2. About the visualizations:

In order to present our big world in a limited 2D graphical approach. I shrink the dimensions and the detail of the existing reality.

Humans and Objects are dots, 3D entities like us become tiny dots (zero dimension) on a 3D space where their activity is backward translated to 2D perspective coordinates

Interactions between two entities are lines, and in our world planes or shapes were formed when interactions involved multiple people or objects. Which becomes an event.

We now as observer from the higher ground can witness the events’ change, progress, and karma by the continuous growth of the plane into various shapes.

Every world we reincarnated back into will have a visual color and an audio color tone. It is considered to be the theme of that particular life.

The final composition becomes a mix of the above, everything is merely the same but everything yet looks different. Depends on your perspective."

3. Some personal sharing thru creating REIN:

Life is short - I am happy if you are feeling annoyed and you feel the screen comes and fades so fast. Indeed this is my personal feeling about life, too short and things ended before you realize it.

Some life is super long and boring - I am also happy if you felt so. So sing and discover your song of life when you are in the room. It happens once only with this combination.

No time to prepare/predict/prejudge - but you can enjoy cause you/he/she/it/they/we will end in here suddenly. So enjoy the up and down, sweet and sour of every bit.

There is always an intangible target and goal preset to you, and it cast a line between you and it. You can choose to ignore it or be actively chasing it. But no matter which choices you made, your locus was left and shown in front of your eyes.

4. Observer’s responsibility and award
This work inspires me that in life we can both be the actors/actress and also the observer.

What matters more to you?
The background, your choice, or both?
Are you the observer guy who sits and doesn’t move?
Are you moving towards the [goal] linking with you? Do you keep chasing it?
Are you caring about the background more? Do you have a feeling they somehow related to you?
Or do you simply move your life freely without caring about the other happening?
Your voice is too loud or not?
Will you find the background noise too loud?
What can you do with it?
If the target connected to you is hollow and empty, would you still care about it?

And Why? Why do you feel so?
Which part of the above dialogue is related to your existing life?
What can we do/change/keep?
What you really can control?"


// [Click] - The sound of the work can be muted by clicking again the screen
// [s] - Take a selfie of this world and you inside
// [spacebar] - you can stop the time and walk/think freely like NEO in the matrix

Behind [REIN]
As a generative artist, I force myself to seek the possible ways to use these tools/skills/presentation forms.

In Traveler, it is about finding the difference between being alone and feeling loneliness
In FEA, it is about possibilities
In BULLET, it is about courage and faith
In REIN, I hope we can treasure what we lost and gained.

Art to me can be the visualization of aesthetics or a mutually enjoyable creative process for you and me.

Or like this time in REIN.

A journey towards our room inside our heart shape box.

metadata.name: Yellow House #85
metadata.description:
It is very easy to forget the beauty of the places we consume because they are available to us by nature.
The things we consume all our lives we find not so special.
It’s very hard to remember how special and valuable these things really are.

With this work, I will try to give sincere admiration and respect to my favorite place on the beach!

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 'f' to save .png with resolution = 4000px x 4000px

Created using p5js ,100% p5.js code and math.

@Mutart, April, 2022.

metadata.name: Divisio(X) #359
metadata.description:
On a dynamic grid (2x2, 3x3, 4x4, 5x5 or 6x6), each cell is filled with one shape (out of 6). For each shape, a rotation (0°, 90°, 180°, 270°) and a stroke weight (from 5 to 100) are applied. A color palette (out of 6) and a number of layers (1 to 3) are applied to the canvas.

The background under the shape can be filled by cells, rows or columns. At times, a thick grid may also be visible.	

Generative abstract compositions. Coded in January 2022.

metadata.name: mountain range #32
metadata.description: Smooth animation of many lines merging into several large ones create an exciting pattern that has a high uniqueness. At the end of the animation, the intricacy of the lines starts to remind me of a mountain range or the human nervous system.

metadata.name: AutomataPunk, The Masquerader #64
metadata.description:
A playful spin on PFPs, and the prevalence of them on social media, especially among the NFT community.
The characters are procedurally generated, and then colored and texturized using 1D Cellular Automata.
Masqueraders hide their rarity scores. The cutest or most unusual one will be the most popular.
Their dimensions are always a multiple of 360.

Controls:
- Press 's' to save a PNG file.
- Press 't' to toggle, for a larger and higher resolution version that once complete can be saved as a 3600x3600 PNG by pressing 's'. In this mode, the Masquerader may become much larger than your screen. Wait for its render to complete before saving it. Toggle back to the regular size by pressing 't' again.

License:
See included LICENSE.md

Credits:
Made in p5js

metadata.name: Ersbla #765
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #302
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: The Arcade State #11
metadata.description:
"The Arcade State is a strange place.
You can only walk in four directions. Which will it be? 
As you make your way across the landscape, you will discover lush grasslands, grim structures, and colorful grounds. And if you get lucky, you might unearth artifacts of other times, hidden deep inside the system."
   - The Architect -


I am an artist and a scientist fueled by challenges. I'm most creative when I can't work under perfect conditions and I have to improvise to find a solution.
For The Arcade State, I constrained myself to only using four angles along the circle (45, 90, 135, and 180 degrees) while still producing interesting images with depth and variety.


Keys:
Press 'e' to export the image in HD  (1600x2000)
Press 'h' to export the image in UHD (4800x6000) - this will take a few seconds
